Hong Kong Aims to Start Short Selling Reporting Rules in 2012

-- B y   M a r c o   L u i
-- 
2011-10-18T09:29:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/hong-kong-aims-to-start-short-selling-reporting-rules-in-2012.html
Hong Kong  aims to implement the
short selling reporting requirements by the end of the first
quarter of 2012, the Securities and Futures Commission said in a
statement on its website.  The regulator is consulting the public on revised rules to
require reporting of net short positions, according to the
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Lui at 
 mlui11@bloomberg.net  